CV
--

FEMNIST (Image Classification)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Model: 2-layer CNN + 2-layer FFN

Args: subsample 5% of the data,  a final dense layer with 2048 units, lr = 0.0003 for fedavg 0.06 for mini-batch SGD, 1000 rounds, use 5 clients per round.

Metric: Accuracy 74.72%

Celeba (Image Classification)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Model: 2-layer CNN + 2-layer FFN

Args: 10 clients per round for 100 rounds, training locally for one epoch with a batch size of 5, lr = 0.001

Metric: Accuracy 89.46%

NLP
---

Shakespeare (Next Character Prediction)
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

Model: LSTM of two layers of 256 units each.

Args:  118 devices (around 5% of the total) in our Shakespeare data; embedding 8, a sequence length of 80 for the LSTM, lr = 0.8, 10 devices per round.

Metric: AccuracyTop1 0.4x-0.5x See fig 2.

Twitter (Sentiment Analysis)
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

Model: a bag of words model with lr

Args: lr = 0.0003

Metric: AccuracyTop1 0.5x-0.6x See fig 3.

Reddit (Language Modeling)
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

Model: LSTM of two layers of 256 units each.

Args:  819 devices and a model similar to the one we described for Shakespeare, embedding is now 200, lr = 4 · 2^0.5, 10 clients per round for 100 rounds, training locally for one epoch using a batch size of 5. 

Metric: AccuracyTop1 13.35%

Synthetic (use FedEM args)
--------------------------

Model: a perceptron with sigmoid activations

Args: :raw-html-m2r:`<del>1, 000 devices, only one cluster, 60 features and 5 classes,  10 clients per round for 100 rounds, trained locally for one epoch with a batch size of 5, lr = 0.1.</del>`
